request.description:
# Instagram Messages API

This API endpoint allows you to send messages on Instagram.

## Request

### Endpoint

`POST https://graph.instagram.com/{{api-version}}/me/messages`

### Request Body

- Type: JSON


| Parameter | Type | Description |
| --- | --- | --- |
| recipient.id | String | The Instagram user ID of the recipient |
| message.attachment.type | String | The type of attachment (e.g. image, video) |
| message.attachment.payload.url | String | The URL of the attachment (e.g. image, video) |

#### Example

``` json
{
    "recipient": {
        "id": "{{instagram_scoped_id}}"
    },
    "message": {
        "attachment": {
            "type": "image",
            "payload": {
                "url": "https://www.example.com/image.jpg"
            }
        }
    }
}
## Response
The response of this request is a JSON object with the following schema:
```json
{
  "recipient_id": "IGSID",
  "message_id": "MESSAGE-ID"
}

 ```

### POST /{{api_version}}/{{ig_user_id}}/messages

This endpoint is used to send a message with an image attachment to a specified recipient on Instagram. The request requires the recipient's ID and the attachment ID of the image being sent.

Please use the Attachment upload Api in this collection to upload a an image and get an attachment id and store the attachment_id in the Environment variable attachment_id of Instagram environment before this api is used

#### Request Body

The request body must be in JSON format and should contain the following structure:

``` json
{
  "recipient": {
    "id": "{{ig_scoped_id}}"
  },
  "message": {
    "attachment": {
      "type": "image",
      "payload": {
        "attachment_id": "{{attachment_id}}"
      }
    }
  }
}

 ```

- **recipient**: An object containing the recipient's information.

    - **id**: (string) The unique identifier of the recipient (Instagram user) to whom the message will be sent.

- **message**: An object that encapsulates the message content.

    - **attachment**: An object that specifies the type of attachment.

        - **type**: (string) The type of the attachment, which in this case is "image".

        - **payload**: An object containing the details of the attachment.

            - **attachment_id**: (string) The unique identifier for the image attachment previously uploadedd using attachment upload api.


#### Response

Upon a successful request, the server responds with a status code of 200 and a JSON object containing the following fields:

``` json
{
  "recipient_id": "{{ig_scoped_id}}",
  "message_id": ""
}

 ```

- **recipient_id**: (string) The unique ig scoped id of the recipient to whom the message was sent.

- **message_id**: (string) The unique identifier of the sent message.


This response confirms that the message was successfully sent to the specified recipient.

For more details on attachment upload api sending a message with an uploaded asset refer to developer documentation at: [https://developers.facebook.com/docs/messenger-platform/reference/attachment-upload-api/](https://developers.facebook.com/docs/messenger-platform/reference/attachment-upload-api/)

